Norileca indica
attaches to the ventral part of the host branchial cavity, with the cephalon to the anterior end of the host, and with its abdomen or brood pouch directed outwards, facing the branchial cavity ( Bruce 1990 ;
Neeraja et al. 2014
;
Rameshkumar et al. 2015
;
Behera et al. 2016
).

Distribution . Record from Mozambique ( Rokicki 1982 ;
Wal et al. 2017
; Avdeev 1978b ) lists the species from north-western Australia and off Sumatra , Indonesia , Philippines and New Guinea ( Trilles 1976 ) and northern Arabian Sea (
Kazmi et al. 2002
). Recent records are from southeast and southwest coast of India (
Rameshkumar et al. 2013d
, 2015 ;
Behera et al. 2016
; Aneesh et al. 2016).
